| Required Info                         |                                                                |
|---------------------------------|------------------------------------------- |
| Camera Model                       | D435 | 
| Firmware Version                   | 05.09.14.00 | 
| Operating System & Version |   Win 10 | 
| Platform                                 | PC  |
| SDK Version                            |  2.15.0.163                          | 
| Language                            |  C# | 

Given the following piece of code
```csharp
void Stream()
{
  using (var ctx = new Context())
  using (var pipe = new Pipeline(ctx))
  {
    var config = new Config();
    config.DisableAllStreams();
    config.EnableStream(Stream.Color, 1280, 720, Format.Bgr8, 30);
    config.EnableStream(Stream.Depth, 1280, 720, Format.Z16, 30);
    pipe.Start(config);

    while (run)
    {
      using (var frame = pipe.WaitForFrames())
      {
        Handle(frame);
      }
    }
  }
}
```

When the camera is unplugged while this loop is running we get an error:
```
Exception thrown: 'System.Exception' in Intel.RealSense.dll
Device disconnected. Failed to recconect: No device connected5000
rs2_pipeline_wait_for_frames(pipe:06413080)
```
This is expected. Once the camera is plugged in again we call the above code again but it fails at `pipe.Start()` with
```
Exception thrown: 'System.Exception' in Intel.RealSense.dll
_source->QueryInterface(__uuidof(IKsTopologyInfo), reinterpret_cast<void **>(&ks_topology_info)) returned: HResult 0x80004002: "No such interface supported"
rs2_pipeline_start_with_config(pipe:07D69BD0, config:07D69B70)
```
This is a regression from 2.13 where calling the above after plugging the camera back in would restart the video stream. Is this intentional? Is there some other way now to continue a stream after reconnecting the camera?

